### Now let's do Hello World!

By using C++, you can easily do this.

	#include <iostream>
	using namespace std;
	int main()
	{
		cout << "Hello World!" << endl;
		return 0;
	}

This is a simple example. If you managed to do it, there would be

	Hello World!

on your screen.

Then let's analysis the code.

	#include <iostream>

The '#' means preprocessing. You can use it to copy a header into your source file with the command 'include'.

'iostream' is a header contains functions and classes and methods of input and output.
